    <p><strong>PhD Researcher – AI-driven Adaptive Water Management</strong></p>
    <p>Goyang, Korea | Phone: +82-10-4412-8470</p>
    <p>Email: taredejum6@gmail.com | tarehydro19@gmail.com</p>

    <p>
        A dedicated PhD researcher developing AI-driven frameworks for hydrological and climate-risk assessment.
        Skilled in integrating process-based models with machine learning, Bayesian inference, TensorFlow,
        and explainable AI (SHAP). Experienced in climate modeling, groundwater sustainability analysis,
        and physics-guided ML for adaptive water management under uncertainty.
    </p>
</section>

